      • getAuditConfiguration

        @GET
 @Path(value="auditConfiguration")
 @Produces(value="application/json")
public javax.ws.rs.core.Response getAuditConfiguration(@QueryParam(value="name")
                                                                                                                                    java.lang.String name,
                                                                                                                                    @DefaultValue(value="false") @QueryParam(value="enabled")
                                                                                                                                    boolean enabled)
                                                                                                                             throws sailpoint.tools.GeneralException
        Following logic is implemented based off the inputs : 1. name = null and enabled = false - return all AuditActions. 2. name = null and enabled = true - return all AuditActions that are enabled. 3. name = foo and enabled = false - return only one AuditActions with name foo if found, else exception. 4. name = foo and enabled = true - return only one AuditActions with name foo if found, else exception.
        Throws:
        sailpoint.tools.GeneralException
